On July 27, 2018, the President signed three bills into law. The first bill, S. 490, allows for the extension of the construction license for the Gibson Dam Hydroelectric Project in Montana. The second bill, S. 931, designates the facility of the United States Postal Service located at 4910 Brighton Boulevard in Denver, Colorado, as the George Sakato Post Office. Lastly, S. 2734 designates the Federal building and United States courthouse located at 1300 Victoria Street in Laredo, Texas, as the George P. Kazen Federal Building and United States Courthouse.